goals.question: What is the relationship between the value and the size of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['size'] = pd.to_numeric(data['size'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["size"].median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the size of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['depth'] = pd.to_numeric(data['depth'], errors='coerce')
    data['size'] = pd.to_numeric(data['size'], errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['depth'], data['size'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the depth and the size of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Depth')
    plt.ylabel('Size')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['children'] = data['children'].apply(lambda x: len(x))
    plt.hist(data['children'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['children'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['children'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['children'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['children'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the number of children for each node in the flare.json dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
